<P>22. The conduct of the defendants as earlier pleaded was high-handed, reprehensible and deliberately undertaken in reckless and complete disregard of the rights of the plaintiffs so as to advance and further the economic and business interests of the defendants and as such is deserving of a substantial award of punitive damages in light of the substantial size of the assets of the defendants which are in excess of seven billion dollars.</P>
<P>23. The damages suffered as earlier pleaded by the plaintiffs were sustained in Ontario, the Agreement was made in Ontario as the communication of the acceptance by Vancity of the plaintiffs' offer, earlier pleaded was received in Ontario by the plaintiff Royal, the breaches of the Agreement earlier pleaded made impossible performance of the Agreement that concerned the issuance of policies of insurance by the plaintiffs which was to occur in both Ontario and British Columbia, the earlier pleaded torts of conspiracy and misrepresentation were committed in Ontario by the defendant VC U, which is in any event a necessary or proper party to this proceeding brought against Co&mdash;operators, 242-Canada, Federated and <UNDER>708- Canada.</UNDER> The plaintiffs rely on Rule 17-02(f)(g)(h)(o) of the Rules of Civil Procedure in support of service of the Notice of Action and this Statement of Claim outside of Ontario.</P>
